// Name: Orion - Artemis II Tracking Script
// Author: Shawn Gano
// License: Public Domain
// Version: 1.1
// Description: Visualizes the location of the Orion Spacecraft during the Artemis II mission. 
//              This script uses a data file generated for a specfic location and specific launch date. Be sure this is correct for your current location. 
//              NOTE: This script loops indefinitely and must be stopped manually (updates 4 times a second).  This updates whenever the time is changed in the GUI.  It is best use while the time is paused and the time is manually changed / stepped.  Be sure to use times during the mission (otherwise there is nothing to see).

// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  Stellarium Script to track Artemis II - loops indefinitely until manually stopped
//
//  Shawn Gano  
//           V1.0: 17 Feb 2026
//           V1.1: 15 Mar 2026 - clean-up / refactoring
//  
//  Place in folder:  '/Applications/Astronomy/ Stellarium.app/Contents/Resources/scripts' (MacOS)
//  
//  In Stellarium press F12 to open Script Console to run / see results as needed
//
//   SCRIPT runs forever, needs to be stopped manually (via F12 console or Configuration Window-> scripts)
//
//  Script API doc:  https://stellarium.org/doc/25.0/scripting.html

// Import custom functions (library) as well as custom data: (be sure both files are located in the same directory as this one)
include("Orion_Artemis_II_Library.inc");
include("Orion_Artemis_II_Data.inc");

// Clear existing custom objects
CustomObjectMgr.removeCustomObjects();

// Example Outputting to Log in Stellarium
core.debug("Running Script to Update Artemis II Location! (Log) -- To stop use the script console (F12)");
core.output("Running Script to Update Artemis II Location! (output) -- To stop use the script console (F12)");


//  ----- TESTING Adding Custom Object: 
//RA/Dec ON DATE is what is entered here....
